      
        
                                                                       DAY 4
                                                             MANAGING CHANGING IN GIT 


1> Modified file = A modified file is a file that has already been committed but has been changed after the last commit.


2> git diff = show the exact difference between the last committed version and the current version of a life.

             purpose: view added lines.
                      view removed lines.
                     compare changes before committing.


3> git restore = it discards uncommitted changes and restores the file to its last committed state.

              purpose : undo accidental changes.
                        recover the last committed version.


4> git rm = removes a tracked file from git and stages the deletionfor the next commit.

                     pupose : delete a tracked file.
                             record the deletion in git history after committing.
